.TH "dev_valid_name" 9 "dev_valid_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_valid_name \- check if name is okay for network device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" dev_valid_name
.BI "(const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
name string

Network device names need to be valid file names to
allow sysfs to work.  We also disallow any kind of
whitespace.
